  <p>
    Most people never see what happens during a septic pump-out — the truck arrives, some time
    passes, and it leaves. But the appointment follows a clear sequence, and understanding it does two
    useful things: it helps you prepare the property so the visit goes quickly and cheaply, and it
    tells you what to ask at the one moment when your tank is actually open and visible.
  </p>

  {/* Intended asset: /images/resources/what-happens-during-a-septic-pumping-appointment-hero.webp — see public/images/resources/README.md */}
  <ResourceImageSlot
    src={"/images/resources/what-happens-during-a-septic-pumping-appointment-hero.webp"}
    alt={"Septic pumping appointment showing a truck, an opened tank lid and a technician servicing the tank"}
    width={1600}
    height={900}
